{
  "texts": [
    "As an ultimate goal beyond the scope of the present study, we wish to understand the competition between several bosonic relaxation channels, e.g., in the presence of phonons and magnons (see [45,46] for work in that direction).To set the stage, we paraphrase results from Ref.",
    "[21], where a charge carrier was initialized in a quasimomentum eigenstate in an empty band and then coupled to optical phonons via a Holstein coupling.",
    "In the adiabatic regime where phonon frequencies ω 0 are smaller than the electronic bandwidth, Ref.",
    "[21] reports a fast relaxation to a quasi-stationary state.",
    "That quasistationary state is characterized by a complete energy transfer from the electron to the optical phonons accompanied by a relaxation of the average electronic momentum to zero."
  ]
}